snippet.textDisplay: I bought Wild Arms 5 the day it came out...don't expect the heart-wrenching masterpiece WA4 was.  It's a standard romp through JRPG fare.  In fact it's almost sickeningly saccharine. If you're a WA fan play it, otherwise it's an easy rental or pass.
